out introducing local interfaces to abstract away concrete client dependencies. 
This is actually a very good architectural improvement - it makes the biz layer 
more testable and reduces coupling.\n\nNow let me check for potential issues:\n1
. The MixingUseCase in biz layer depends on eventbus.StreamPublisher and eventbu
s.EventAdapter - this could be considered an architecture issue if the project s
trictly enforces that biz layer should not depend on infrastructure/pkg. However
, eventbus is a cross-cutting concern and these are interfaces, so it\'s arguabl
e.\n2. Let me check if there\'s any direct data layer access from service or biz
that shouldn\'t be there.\n3. MarketService has direct access to repo.MarketRepo
, repo.UserFishRepo, etc. - this is actually a service layer accessing data laye
r directly, which violates the typical layered architecture (Service → Biz → Rep
o → Data). However, this might be existing code pattern in the project.\n\nWait,
